      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "c. M. Levey, third vice presi-\ndent of the Northern Pacific, has\nsent word to Mayor Daggett that\nplans for the raising of the tracks\nthrough Spokane would be for\nwarded to him within a few days.\nThe last plans of the railroad met\ngeneral disapproval and were not\naccepted. The present plan is to\nraise the track eight feet and to\nmake subway in the street, eight\nfeet."
